The paper deals with natural language understanding and dialogue systems, which are typically studied in the sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of neural networks for denotation extraction, which falls under the sub-category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the need for large amounts of training data, which is a common problem in Information Retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper discusses the use of interactive learning and user data, which is relevant to Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC).
